In small bowl, combine seasoning ingredients; press into both sides of beef steaks. Let stand 10 minutes. Meanwhile in medium bowl, combine relish ingredients; cover and refrigerate. Place steaks on grid over medium, ash-covered coals. Grill, uncovered, 11 to 14 minutes for medium rare to medium doneness, turning once. Place steaks on platter; spoon relish next to steaks. Garnish with lemon and cucumber slices and mint or parsley sprigs.